<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/223:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the American Delegate (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to">Wilson</persName>)</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-06T14:00:00-05:00">December
                                    6, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>259. Your 473, December 5, 10 p.m. Department has not received a copy of
                            the Japanese naval proposal. Please telegraph text if it is of
                            reasonable length; otherwise telegraph a summary and follow with full
                            text by open mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>